.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
For all
\&\s-2\u[1]\d\s+2[IMAGE]\&\s-2\u[2]\d\s+2 [$j$]\-th variates associated to the
.PP
\fBEquation 1.45. \fR \&\s-2\u[3]\d\s+2.sp .RS 4 [IMAGE]\&\s-2\u[4]\d\s+2 \e[ \elambda = \einf\eleft\e{ l \eleft| \efrac{1}{\ebar{w}_n}\esum_{i=1}^{l} w_i \egeq \ealpha \eright\&. \eright\e} \e] .RE
.PP
smallest samples (left tail) or the weighted mean of the
.PP
\fBEquation 1.46. \fR \&\s-2\u[5]\d\s+2.sp .RS 4 [IMAGE]\&\s-2\u[6]\d\s+2 \e[ n + 1 \- \erho = n + 1 \- \esup\eleft\e{ r \eleft| \efrac{1}{\ebar{w}_n}\esum_{i=r}^{n} w_i \egeq (1 \- \ealpha) \eright\&. \eright\e} \e] .RE
.PP
largest samples (right tail), the absolute weighted tail means
\&\s-2\u[7]\d\s+2[IMAGE]\&\s-2\u[8]\d\s+2 [$\widehat{ATM}_{n,\alpha}(X, j)$]
are computed and returned as an iterator range\&. Alternatively, the relative weighted tail means
\&\s-2\u[9]\d\s+2[IMAGE]\&\s-2\u[10]\d\s+2 [$\widehat{RTM}_{n,\alpha}(X, j)$]
are returned, which are the absolute weighted tail means normalized with the weighted (non\-coherent) sample tail mean
\&\s-2\u[11]\d\s+2[IMAGE]\&\s-2\u[12]\d\s+2 [$\widehat{NCTM}_{n,\alpha}(X)$]\&.
.PP
\fBEquation 1.47. \fR \&\s-2\u[13]\d\s+2.sp .RS 4 [IMAGE]\&\s-2\u[14]\d\s+2 \e[ \ewidehat{ATM}_{n,\ealpha}^{\emathrm{right}}(X, j) = \efrac{1}{\esum_{i=\erho}^n w_i} \esum_{i=\erho}^n w_i \exi_{j,i} \e] .RE
